2.02	Berlin_tram	Berlin tram	The Berlin tram network (German: ) is the main tram system in Berlin, Germany. It is one of the oldest tram networks in the world having its origins in 1865 and is operated by (BVG), which was founded in 1929. It is notable for being one of the largest tram systems; there are 22 tram lines operate across a standard gauge network with 382 stops and measuring 191.6 kilometres in length. Nine of the lines are operated 24 hours per day, identified with the letter 'M' before their number.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6d/Flexitityberlin.jpg/300px-Flexitityberlin.jpg
